# new-api Integration

This project is a **refactor of new-api**, not a rewrite. new-api's mature
subsystems are the source of truth — reuse them, never rebuild or duplicate.

## Reuse (do NOT reinvent)

- Users, tokens, login/OAuth/2FA/passkey, sessions.
- Recharge/top-up, subscription/membership, redemption codes, payments.
- Channels, channel groups, model ratios, the React admin console (`web/default`).
- Quota/ledger: this gateway is the **billing authority**, implemented on top of
  new-api's existing quota system — extend it, do not fork a parallel ledger.

## Build (the enhanced data plane)

- The pipeline/hook/event/plugin framework and the observable relay path.
- Existing `relay/channel` `Adaptor`s become upstream-adapter plugins.

## Security invariants

- The real upstream target comes only from server-side Provider/Channel config.
  Never read the upstream target from client headers/query (open-proxy / SSRF).
- External URL downloads go through the SSRF-safe client (allowlist, no private/
  metadata IPs, redirect re-validation).

See `docs/integration-newapi.md` for the concrete mapping and phased plan.
